      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🔴 Critical] Line 1910: The public API can trigger a re-bootstrap of every shared conversation with `uri` on every call, with no validation, throttling, or deduplication. A client repeatedly calling this for a contact with many swarms could create excessive network activity and duplicate sync work. Please reject empty/invalid peer URIs and gate repeated syncs per peer/conversation, or reuse an existing pending-bootstrap/fetch mechanism before calling `bootstrap`.\\n```suggestion\\nif (uri.empty()) {\\n    JAMI_WARN(\\\"[Account {}] Ignoring sync request with empty peer URI\\\", pimpl_-\u003eaccountId_);\\n    return;\\n}\\n// Also skip conversations already being bootstrapped/fetched for this peer.\\n```",
